<concept id="concept_180F6F1C25B84920842366B7499D48C4">
  <title>Custom Events (Counter)</title>
  <shortdesc>The number of times an event occurs. For example, if event1 is set
	 to count the number of times a document is downloaded, then the 
	 <wintitle>Custom Event</wintitle> report for Event 1 shows the total number
	 of times the event (or download) occurs. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Metrics" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody>
    <table id="table_F68E5D19862844159D8CC14400A6EC4A">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="1.00*" />
        <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="2.34*" />
        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry colname="col1">Uses 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col2">Description 
				</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry colname="col1">Traffic 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col2">Each time an event is set, an instance is
				  counted for the event. Uses allocation only. 
				</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry colname="col1">Conversion 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col2">Each time an event is set, an instance is
				  counted for the event. Does not use allocation. 
				</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry colname="col1">Ad Hoc Analysis 
				</entry>
            <entry colname="col2">Each time an event is set, an instance is
				  counted for the event. All allocation metrics are available for each event. 
				</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
  </conbody>
